<title>GERMANY: Dywidag head upbeat on German builders.</title>
<headline>Dywidag head upbeat on German builders.</headline>
<dateline>DUESSELDORF, Germany 1997-07-07</dateline>
<text>
<p>The chairman of German building group Dyckerhoff &amp; Widmann AG, Hans-Joachim Wolff, said on Monday he was confident about prospects for the German building industry.</p>
<p>Wolff told the Handelsblatt newspaper that in addition to greater efforts in overseas markets, German builders were likely to profit from new niche markets at home.</p>
<p>Separately, the Federal Statistics Office said the building price index for homes fell 0.7 percent in May from the same month a year ago.</p>
<p>In east Germany, the index fell one percent and in west Germany it declined 0.6 percent.</p>
<p>--Frankfurt Newsroom +49 69 756525</p>
